    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## 2. Bouncing Ball — Multiple Bounces\n\nTo simulate repeated bounces, we use the stateful API: `np_cvode_create` builds a persistent integrator, `np_cvode_step` advances it segment-by-segment, and `np_cvode_reinit` resets the state after each impact (reversing the velocity with coefficient of restitution $e = 0.8$). Reusing one handle across all bounces avoids the cost of rebuilding the linear solver and re-registering events on each segment.\n\nWe also pass `rootdir = [-1]` so CVODE only detects falling crossings of $h$. Without this, the post-bounce state $h = 0,\\ v > 0$ sits exactly on the event surface and would re-trigger immediately.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Multi-bounce via stateful CVODE handle.\n   rootdir = [-1] only fires on falling crossings of bh, so the post-bounce\n   state (bh = 0, bv > 0) doesn't immediately re-trigger the root. */\ncor : 0.8$\nt_end : 8.0$\ndt : 0.01$\n\nt_all : [0.0]$  h_all : [10.0]$  v_all : [0.0]$\nevent_times : []$\n\nsolver : np_cvode_create([bv, -g], [bt, bh, bv],\n                         [10.0, 0.0], 0.0,\n                         1e-12, 1e-12, adams, [bh], 5000, [-1])$\n\nt_now : 0.0$\nwhile t_now < t_end do block([res, ev],\n  res : np_cvode_step(solver, min(t_now + dt, t_end)),\n  if length(res[3]) > 0 then (\n    /* An event fired during this step.  Record the event point and\n       reinit; the integrator continued past the event to res[1]\n       without knowing about the bounce, so we discard that state. */\n    ev : first(res[3]),\n    event_times : endcons(ev[1], event_times),\n    t_now : ev[1],\n    t_all : endcons(ev[1], t_all),\n    h_all : endcons(ev[2][1], h_all),\n    v_all : endcons(ev[2][2], v_all),\n    np_cvode_reinit(solver, ev[1], [0.0, -cor * ev[2][2]])\n  ) else (\n    t_now : res[1],\n    t_all : endcons(res[1], t_all),\n    h_all : endcons(res[2][1], h_all),\n    v_all : endcons(res[2][2], v_all)\n  )\n)$\n\nprintf(true, \"~d bounces detected~%\", length(event_times))$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 14,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "4 bounces detected\no130$$\\mathbf{false}$$\nfalse"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
